718,"23. RAMOS GIN FIZZ
","23. RAMOS GIN FIZZ
",RAMOS GIN FIZZ,"Fun fact: Whenever legendary Louisiana governor Huey P. Long traveled to New York City, he took his own New Orleans bartender so he could have this drink made right.
 1 1/2 ounces gin
 2 tablespoons cream
 1/2 ounce lemon juice
 1 egg white
 1 tablespoon powdered sugar
 3 to 4 drops of orange flower water 1/2 ounce lime juice 1/4 ounce club soda
  Fill cocktail shaker with ice.
  Add gin, cream, lemon juice, egg white, powdered sugar, orange flower water, and lime juice.
  Shake.
  Strain into a goblet.
  Top with chilled club soda.
